#hm-note[
  Month 4 opens Quarter II. It is primarily philosophical and meditative, but its
  philosophical depth is the foundation for everything that follows in Quarters
  II and III. The seed theory of metals is not an abstraction — it is the
  operative framework that tells the practitioner what they are actually doing
  when they conduct Via Humida cycles: not merely dissolving and recrystallising,
  but assisting the mineral's own developmental process. That shift in
  understanding changes the quality of attention brought to the work.
]

